<p><strong>Skills</strong> Perception +4, Stealth +5</p>

<p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft.</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 1 (200 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Hold Breath.</em></strong> While out of water, the octopus can hold its breath for 1 hour.</p>

<p><strong><em>Underwater Camouflage.</em></strong> The octopus has advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks made while underwater.</p>

<p><strong><em>Water Breathing.</em></strong> The octopus can breathe only underwater.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Tentacles.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 15 ft., one target. Hit: 10 (2d6 + 3) bludgeoning damage. If the target is a creature, it is grappled (escape DC 16). Until this grapple ends, the target is restrained, and the octopus canâ€™t use its tentacles on another target.</p>

<p><strong><em>Ink Cloud (Recharges after a Short or Long Rest).</em></strong> A 20-foot-radius cloud of ink extends all around the octopus if it is underwater. The area is heavily obscured for 1 minute, although a significant current can disperse the ink. After releasing the ink, the octopus can use the Dash action as a bonus action.</p>

